.TH SARIF-REPLAY-16 "1" "November 2025" "Debian 16-20251130-1 16.0.0 20251130 (experimental) [master r16-5779-gc6af130047a]" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sarif-replay-16 \- Replay results from one or more .sarif files as if they were GCC diagnostics
.SH DESCRIPTION
sarif\-replay [OPTIONS] FILE+
.IP
"Replay" results from one or more .sarif files as if they were
GCC diagnostics
.SH OPTIONS
.HP
\fB\-fdiagnostics\-add\-output\fR=\fI\,SCHEME\/\fR
.IP
Add an additional output sink when replaying diagnostics, as
per the gcc option
.HP
\fB\-fdiagnostics\-color=\fR{never|always|auto}
.TP
Control colorization of diagnostics.
Default: auto.
.HP
\fB\-fjson\-comments\fR
.IP
Support C and C++ style comments in .sarif JSON files
.HP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
.IP
Print notes about each .sarif file before and after replaying it.
.HP
\fB\-\-echo\-file\fR
.IP
Print the filename and file contents to stderr before replaying it.
.HP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
.IP
Print version and exit.
.HP
\fB\-\-usage\fR
.IP
Print this message and exit.
.PP
Options for maintainers:
.HP
\fB\-fdebug\-physical\-locations\fR
.IP
Dump debugging information about physical locations to stderr.
